html.ogDescription:
Blurred Lines by Renee Campbell is the 5th drop in the Here for the Art collection curated by GM Farcaster.

Here for the Art is a collection celebrating the artists of the Farcaster ecosystem. Each month, an exclusive piece is airdropped to GM Farcaster wowow hypersub holders. In addition to the art drop, GM Farcaster records a podcast with the artist and that is also airdropped to all holders of this piece.

Renee Campbell can be found on Farcaster at: @reneecampbell at https://warpcast.com/reneecampbell and her channels /reneecampbell and /flora

Blurred Lines by Renee Campbell - artist statement

When I was asked for an image that I felt most suited Farcaster, at first my mind drew a blank. I thought, what piece of my work could possibly represent Farcaster? Then this image popped into mind. To me it felt like the perfect representation of FC, calm and frantic at the same time. Like a duck looking relaxed while feverishly paddling under water.

I shot this photo of homegrown poppies using a technique called  ICM - intentional camera movement. I‚Äôve been experimenting with this style a lot this year and love that it makes me feel such a mix of feelings with its dynamic movement captured in the still. I couldn‚Äôt think of a better way to describe my experience on Farcaster. Everything constantly moving and growing like flowers caught in the wind but rooted firmly in the ground.

text: THEY ALL HAVE MATCHING RAIN JACKETS !!

I‚Äôm excited to announce that Launchcaster has been acquired by Orange DAO.

We launched Launchcaster two years ago because we didn‚Äôt have a great place to share and discover crypto projects with a community that cared. Since then, our side project has evolved into a public good, fostering thousands of launches and attracting over 15,000 crypto builders.

We wanted to find a long-term home for Launchcaster where it could grow and continue as a public good for crypto builders without needing to turn into some short-term speculative experiment. Just as YC runs Hacker News and Hyper runs Product Hunt, Orange DAO running Launchcaster is a perfect fit!
